President Obama has declared a major disaster in Guam and ordered federal aid to assist in recovery efforts from Typhoon Dolphin, which occurred from May 13-16, 2015. Federal funding will be provided to the territory and eligible local governments for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Rosalyn L. Cole has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.